1.12.2.2.0:
A revive! Hurray!! I've been working on this update for about a month now, so you better appreciate it.
Added:
Improved /btp.
Improved warps, they will now work through dimensions.
Improved tpa system, it'll now work through dimensions.
Improved /explode, added two more arguments, damage terrain and launch.
Improved /enchant, it can now enchant up to level 32767 instead of 127.
Improved /sudo, you can now force other players to send a plain message as well.
Improved /fireball, it got more or less rewritten and added two arguments, speed and impacts
Improved /item, it can now give potions as well.
Improved /killall, it now supports wider ranges, e.g. monster, animal and creature.
Improved /suicide, it now shows its own death message rather than saying you fell off of the world.
Improved /makeunbreakable, you can now undo your actions, unless you made everything unbreakable with a wildcard.
Improved /morecommandspermissions, it'll now show pages instead of dumping all permissions at once when listing permissions.
Added /cannon Fire primed TNT in whatever direction you're looking.
Added /clone Clone the entity you're looking at or the entities matching the given selector.
Added /ctopevents Shows the top 10 events fired on the client.
Added /cyclepainting Cycle through the paintings on whatever panting you're looking at.
Added /defuse Kills any within range or all primed TNT entities and drops a TNT item in its place.
Added /dimension Teleport to a dimension.
Added /dropstore Drop all your items in a chest either at the given location or your location, can optionally clear your inventory as well.
Added /enderchest Open your enderchest or someone else's from anywhere.
Added /extinguish Extinguish yourself if you're on fire.
Added /fakeplayer Create a fakeplayer to e.g. keep chunks loaded or for grinders.
Added /inspect Get any player's known NBT data, online or offline. You may want to run /save before doing so to get the latest data.
Added /invsee See and edit any player's inventory.
Added /jump Teleport wherever you're looking.
Added /macro A client side command to run multiple commands at once.
Added /moar Set the count of your currently active item stack to its max.
Added /potion Create your own potions with many effects and custom colours.
Added /reach Set your reach distance, this works better on 1.12+.
Added /recipe Get the recipe of anything that's either potions, crafting or smelting.

That's it! Releases for other versions should be expected during the next weeks/months.

1.12.1.1.10:
Added:
/break Breaks the block you're looking at.
/spawn Teleports you to spawn.
/wild Teleports you randomly in the world.
/ptime <day/night/normal/6900> Sets your personal time, can be used on any server. I am not responsible if you get banned because of this.
1.12.1.1.11:
Added:
/smite <player> Strikes someone with lightning.
/through Teleports you through a wall.

Fixed:
All commands which you were supposed to be able to use on singleplayer or modded server not being able to use.
TL;DR a lot of permission issues.
1.12.1.1.12:
Added:
/hat Puts the item you're holding on your head.
/repair Repairs the item you're holding
/rename <name> Renames the item you're holding, you can use color codes like &1, &2, &3, etc.
1.12.1.1.13:
Added:
/powertool <command> Assigns a command to the item you're holding using NBT.
/resetnbt Resets the NBT data of the item you're holding.
/shownbt Shows the NBT data of the item you're holding.

Changes:
The mod is now usable for any Minecraft version ranging from 1.11 to 1.12.
1.12.1.1.14:
Added:
/vanish Makes you invisible, you basically get the invisibility potion effect but without the potion effect.
/setfov <fov> Sets your fov, client sided command.
/setrenderdistance <distance> Sets your render distance, client sided command.
/descend Teleports you down 1 floor.
/ascend Teleports you up 1 floor.
/optool Enchants whatever tool your holding with every enchantment of level 16348.
/superpickaxe Makes you able to destroy any block with any pickaxe.

Changed/fixed:
Some small things which I forgot what they were.
1.12.1.1.15:
Added:
/calc <equation> Calculates a math equation so you don't have to.
/optool Enchants the item you're holding with every enchantment of level 16348.

Changed:
The registering of the commands now looks a lot cleaner altough you won't notice this in-game.
1.12.1.1.15.1:
Fixed:
Game crashing when trying to break a block.
1.12.1.1.16:
Added:
/time fix <value> Fixes the time to the set amount.
/enchant <player> <id> [level] Same as the normal command but now you can enchant any item with any enchantment of any level.
/serverstatus Shows the server statuses of all mojang and minecraft servers. Client sided command.
/pastnames [player] Shows the past names of the given player, player defaults to you. Client sided command.
1.12.1.1.17:
Added:
/fireball Summons a fireball in the direction you're looking.
The ability to sit on stairs.
1.12.1.1.17.1:
Changed:
The arrow will now be removed once you dismount the chair or go sit on another one.
1.12.1.1.18:
Added:
/urban <search term> Lookup a word on urban dictionary.

Changed:
The mod can now be used on 1.12.1.
1.12.1.1.19:
Added:
/whereami Shows your coordinates.
/whois <player> Get all of a player's information, including their ip, you hackerman.
/compareips <player1> <player2> Compares the ip addresses of 2 players to see if an account is an alt account of someone.
1.12.1.1.20:
Added:
/narrate [message] Let the narrator narrate a message for you, just doing /narrate makes you able to let it narrate a whole novel. This command does not work on Minecraft versions below 1.12.

Changed:
A very, very lazy way of registering the commands so now whenever I create a new class I don't have to change initialize.java and it'll just get registered when I relog :D (it did take me numerous hours before I achieved this.)
If your game crashes whenever you updated to 1.20, just restart and there shouldn't be a problem.
1.12.1.1.21:
Added:
/download <url> Downloads a file for you.

Changed:
A bit of code cleanup.
1.12.1.1.21.1:
Fixed:

A permission error in the download command.
The narrate command being able to be used on 1.11 and 1.11.2
1.12.1.1.22:
Added:
/copy <text> Copies text.
/tpchunk <x> <y> <z> Teleports you to a chunk.
/crash [description] Crashes your game.

'Fixed':
The game crashing when used for the first time, the commands just don't load but it does prevent the game from crashing.
1.12.1.1.22.1:
Fixed:
The client event handler not being registered correctly, meaning it only loads when you're playing on singleplayer.
1.12.1.1.23:
Added:
/biometeleport <biome> Attempts to teleport you to the given biome.
/fps Shows your fps.
/morecommandsinfo Shows info on your build of MoreCommands.

Changed:
A lot of small things in some commands and some code cleanup.
1.12.1.1.24:
Added:
/tobinary <text> Converts text to binary.
/frombinary <text> Converts text from binary.
/broadcast <text> Broadcasts text.
/makeunbreakable <block> Makes a block unbreakable.

Fixed:
The mod once again not loading on servers and a lot of bugs that only occured on servers.
1.12.1.1.25:
Added:
/home [player] Teleports you to your home.
/sethome Sets your home.
/delhome Deletes your home.
/warp [name] Teleports you to a warp or lists all warps.
/setwarp <name> Sets a warp.
/delwarp <name> Deletes a warp.
/toggleinfooverlay Toggles the info overlay, this overlay is fully customizable in .minecraft/config/MoreCommands/infoOverlay.txt. This overlay will also pop up by pressing C.
/chelp Just like the help command, but for client sided commands.
1.12.1.1.26:
Added:
PERMISSIONS! :D. You can clearly tell I have ran out of ideas, with this permissions system comes a /mcperms command.
Some more functions to the info overlay.

Fixed:
Your game crashing when the homes.yaml and warps.yaml files were empty.
1.12.1.1.26.1:
Fixed:
The mod not working, thanks for not telling, everyone!
1.12.1.1.27:
Added:
ALIASES! :D, with this comes a client-sided /alias command.
Some more functionality to the info overlay.

Fixed:
Some bugs.
1.12.1.1.28:
Added:
Just press esc ingame :3

Fixed:
Some server-sided bugs.
1.12.1.1.29:
Added:
/download can now download YouTube videos, except for music videos.

Fixed:
Some small bugs, like permissions not working on LAN.
